net.ssehub.comani.data

Class Commit

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.ssehub.comani.data.Commit

  • public class Commit
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a commit of a version control system. Objects of this class act as containers for passing information of single commits, like the date of the commit, the affected files, and the introduced changes, from a commit extractor to a commit analyzer.
    Author:
    Christian Kroeher

      • Commit

        public Commit(java.lang.String id,
              java.lang.String date,
              java.lang.String[] commitHeader,
              java.util.List<ChangedArtifact> changedArtifacts)
        Constructs a new commit based on the given information.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of this commit, e.g., as generated by the version control system; should never be null
        date - the date this commit was submitted to the version control system; should never be null
        commitHeader - the header of this commit containing general information, like author, commit message, etc.; should never be null
        changedArtifacts - a list of ChangedArtifacts changed by this commit; can be null
